name: hummingbird-ml
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "hummingbird-ml" %}
{% set version = "0.4.5" %}


package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/{{ name[0] }}/{{ name }}/hummingbird-ml-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: afdaaa35a3e4bde508737fd69def70185ca78c7d140b404148fc7f3fdff0be99

build:
  number: 0
  noarch: python
  script: {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . -vv

requirements:
  host:
    - pip
    - python >=3.6
  run:
    - protobuf >=3.20.0,<=3.20.1
    - dill
    - numpy >=1.15
    - onnxconverter-common >=1.6.0,<=1.11.0
    - psutil
    - python >=3.6
    - scikit-learn
    - scipy
    - pytorch >1.7.0
    # - xgboost >=0.90
    # - skl2onnx >=1.7.0
    # - pytest 
    # - pyspark <3.1.2,>=2.4.4
    # - pyarrow >1.0
    # - prophet ==1.0.1
    # - pre-commit 
    # - onnxruntime >=1.0.0
    # - onnxmltools >=1.6.0
    # - memory-profiler 
    # - lightgbm >=2.2
    # - flake8 
    # - coverage 

test:
  imports:
    - hummingbird.ml
  commands:
    - pip check
  requires:
    - pip

about:
  home: https://github.com/microsoft/hummingbird
  summary: Convert trained traditional machine learning models into tensor computations
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - xhochy
